# 03. Delegation_Model — Implementation Tutorial

## Overview

This tutorial explains how to implement the Delegation Model used in the Northbridge Active Directory lab.

The goal is to simulate a real enterprise scenario where:
- Helpdesk handles daily support tasks
- HR manages identity lifecycle
- Managers have visibility but no control

Everything is implemented using security groups, OU-level delegation, PowerShell, dsacls, and validated from real user accounts.

---

## Environment

- Domain: northbridge.local
- Domain Controller: Windows Server 2022
- Client: Windows 11
- Tools: PowerShell, RSAT, ActiveDirectory module, dsacls

---

## Step 1 — Verify Existing Environment

Before starting, confirm the environment is working correctly.

Run:

Import-Module ActiveDirectory  
Get-ADDomain  

Validate OUs:

Get-ADOrganizationalUnit -Filter * | Select Name,DistinguishedName | Sort Name  

Validate users:

Get-ADUser -Filter * -SearchBase "OU=1.NB_Users,DC=northbridge,DC=local" -Properties Department,Title,Manager | Select SamAccountName,Department,Title,Manager | Sort Department  

Image: images/01-ad-current-structure.png

